                            <comment id="270356" author="jfilizetti" created="Fri, 15 May 2020 18:41:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While this patch is much simpler and works around the issue, I would argue that it&apos;s incorrect.&#160; I can see no use of a hash algorithm in the kernel who implements the functionality but pretends it does not own the algorithm.&#160; Even though these are CRC&apos;s using the crypto hash APIs, is there a belief that at some point when Lustre is attempted to be upstreamed this would be accepted?&#160; I can&apos;t imagine this being accepted as is, but I&apos;m by no means an expert.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
